ros workspace that loads a lanelet2 map into rvizz.

Make sure you have the following thingsL:

install rosnoetic run - sudo apt install ros-noetic-desktop if that doesn't you might have to go to https://wiki.ros.org/noetic/Installation/Ubuntu and follow the instuctions
after install run source /opt/ros/noetic/setup.bash (have to do this everytime you start a new terminal)
you might need to run - "sudo apt install rospy"
you shouldnt need to isntall lanelet2 since its included in the repo already
then make sure you git clone the repo
RUN THE FOLLOWING COMMANDS:

cd ~/catkin_ws
catkin_make (might take a while)
source devel/setup.bash (run everytime you want to work on the workspace/open a new terminal)
roslaunch lanelet_map_viz visualize.launch map_file:=/home//catkin_ws/src/lanelet_map_viz/maps/new_lanelet2_maps.osm frame_id:=map
Rvizz should open after that(make sure to change username to whatever your username is in linux or just copy the path of the new_lanelet2_maps.osm after the equal. in rviz click add in the bottom left go to "by topics" and add the lanelet_markers , markerArray you should see things in the display might need to zoom out a tadbit.

To add more nodes to the workspace add run:

cd ~/catkin_ws/src
catki_create_pkg pospy std_msgs geometry_msgs
add python script in the src folder
make py file executable with chmod
cd ~/catkin_ws
catkin_make
source devel/setup.bash
add launch folder
add launch file in folder
